# BoardGameNexus — Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
Django 6.0.2 board game community platform. PostgreSQL. Bootstrap 5 + crispy-forms.
Apps: games, events, web, accounts (NEW), api (NEW), reviews (NEW).
Custom user model: accounts.CustomUser (extends AbstractUser).

## Core Conventions
- Use Class-Based Views (CBVs) as the primary approach (~90%). Use LoginRequiredMixin and UserPassesTestMixin for auth guards. Use mixins over repeated code.
- All views must be registered in each app's urls.py using path(). Use app_name = 'appname' for namespacing.
- Models go in models.py. Each model needs __str__, Meta class with ordering and verbose_name/verbose_name_plural.
- Forms go in forms.py. Always define clean() or clean_<field>() with user-friendly error messages.
- Never hardcode secrets. All config via os.environ.get(). 
- Template inheritance: all templates extend base.html. Partials start with underscore (_partial.html).
- Static files: project-level in static/. App-level in <app>/static/<app>/.
- Media files: MEDIA_ROOT = BASE_DIR / 'media'. Serve via settings during dev.
- Tests: use Django TestCase. Place in each app's tests.py. Test models, views, and forms separately.

## Django App Structure (each app must have)
models.py, views.py, urls.py, forms.py, admin.py, apps.py, tests.py, migrations/

## CBV Patterns to Use
- ListView for list pages (games, events, reviews)
- DetailView for detail pages
- CreateView + LoginRequiredMixin for create
- UpdateView + LoginRequiredMixin + UserPassesTestMixin for edit (owner-only)
- DeleteView + LoginRequiredMixin + UserPassesTestMixin for delete (owner-only)
- TemplateView for static pages
- FormView for complex forms without a model
- Use get_queryset() to filter, get_context_data() to pass extra context

## Auth Pattern
AUTH_USER_MODEL = 'accounts.CustomUser'
Login URL: /accounts/login/
After login redirect: /
Groups: 'Moderators' (can edit/delete any content), 'Members' (can manage own content)

## DRF Pattern
- Serializers in api/serializers.py
- Views in api/views.py using ModelViewSet or APIView
- URLs in api/urls.py, included under /api/v1/
- Use IsAuthenticatedOrReadOnly permission by default
- Use SessionAuthentication + BasicAuthentication

## Celery Pattern
- Tasks in <app>/tasks.py
- Use @shared_task decorator
- Broker: Redis (CELERY_BROKER_URL from env)
- Task examples: send_welcome_email(user_id), send_weekly_digest()

## Template Conventions
- Load templatetags at top: {% load game_filters %} or {% load static %}
- Show/hide nav links based on {% if user.is_authenticated %}
- Every page has nav + footer (inherited from base.html)
- Error messages: {% if messages %}{% for message in messages %}...{% endfor %}{% endif %}
- Forms: use {% crispy form %} with crispy-forms

## DO NOT
- Do not use function-based views except for very simple utility views
- Do not put business logic in templates
- Do not use raw SQL (use ORM)
- Do not hardcode URLs (use reverse() or {% url %})
- Do not skip migrations after model changes